This is an example of using an App Script that deletes a specific row of a MySQL Database based off of particular cell in a Google Sheet.
Step-by-step guide
 
Set a button in Google Sheets to call the following function
The Delete statement is Deleting all the rows that contain data based off of 1 column which happen to be the first three Columns in this example.
Also Note the “0” that is in “ss.getSheets()[0]”
This “0” refers to the sheet that your grabbing the fields off of.
